        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 18 at 6:49PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 649 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Organ Cave, or near Ronceverte, moving east at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Greenbrier State Forest...
Organ Cave...
Roaring Mountain Summit...
and Glace.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
